span class=title> Trapping a spirit</span><hr size=1> The gathering convened in the Arena. The priestess Ankhami sat on the throne with two knights, Kazanti from the Conclave of the Damned, and Velsor from Indigo Void to guard her, and a mage, Talru, to dispell any foul magics placed on her. Hidden from view, two more wait. Silenae, a bonedancer from the Conclave, and bound to Kallee as the sacrifice, and Shintou, a Knight from the League of shadows, also with ties to Kallee, as the one to kill whichever body the spirit controls.<br>
Without hesitation, Kallee steps before the assembly and kneels before the Priestess. She too is not alone. She brought the Scoundrel Falhurst with her.<br>
<br>
The priestess speaks :'I have brought you here this day to gift you. Your gift is the freedom from Darga. This is your desire, aye?'<br>
<br>
'This is a gift I have long prayed for, Priestess.', Kallee replies. The Priestess nods: 'then it shall be done. There has to be a sacrifice...Innoruuk has spoken', she mentiones.<br>
<br>
Kallee watches the Priestess as Silenae steps forward.. unseen to most eyes, and then appears to Kallee's left, nodding.<br>
She speaks 'aye...a sacrifice, the gods do not intervien with out one', while all eyes are on her.<br>
Disbelief sets in, and Kallee exclaims 'No', looking to the Priestess for help.<br>
<br>
Silenae speaks up, 'Look at me, Kallee.', and Kallee turns towards her. 'It has to be.'<br>
She can sense Kallee's reluctance, and adds 'You have made a vow, Kallee. I hold you to it.'<br>
Silenae stares into Kallee's eyes, as Kallee asks 'You....oh...No. I cannot...this is the price?'<br>
She replies with a trembling voice 'Yes.. and i will ask even more than that.'<br>
<br>
Kallee shakes her head slowly, tears filling her eyes. '....more?'<br>
'You.. have to release control, Kallee.. I have to face her.' is the reply she gets.<br>
<br>
Kallee nods slowly, accepting the need, and she relinquishes control of her body.<br>
Kallee's body trembles slightly, her eyes rolling into the back of her head.<br>
Kallee head rolls back for a moment, then snaps forward, a sneer playing on her lips.<br>
<br>
The reaction to this change are different for all. Talru, the mage shivers at what he sees. Silenae steps away from Kallee, watching her. Just Falhurst belives nothing, and rolls his eyes.<br>
<br>
Darga hisses 'This is what you lead my daughter to then? A silly gathering of silly Tier`Dal. How quaint.'<br>
Calmly, Silenae replies 'Quaint indeed, Darga. But you are powerless before us.'<br>
'Nonsense. I will sacrifice you. I will sacrifice the lot of you. You waste my time here. My time, and Kallee's time.'<br>
The mage sneers, and Darga whirls around, hissing 'You first, worthless one.', while pointing at him. He shakes his head to deny her.<br>
Silenae says 'Oh.. you sacrifice me ? And what do you think you can accomplish there ?'<br>
'You can touch this body, Darga. But you dont have the power to sacrifice me. You.. you can never touch my soul.'<br>
<br>
Her voice filled with contempt, Darga replies 'I am not here to accomplish a thing! It is only Kallee.'<br>
'She drags me here thinking that some foolish Priestess has the power to banish me. You do not understand what I am capable of.'<br>
<br>
'I understand what you think you can do.' Silenae comments, earning a raised eyebrow from Darga. 'you are a fool, Darga. You can hardly control Kallee.. '<br>
As if to prove a point, she summons forth poison, but the spell does not touch Darga.<br>
<br>
'Is that all?', she sneers at Silenae, laughing, but the laugh is cut short as her spirit is tapped into. 'does that feel better, Darga ?' is the only comment made by Silenae. Darga asks 'Do you really want this?', showing the gleaming sword to Silenae, who taunts her 'try to reach my soul, Darga.. if you can'<br>
<br>
Thus the battle is joined. Back and forth it rages, although something seems to hold Darga back - she does not fight witht he full strength Kallee would have had.<br>
<br>
'all you can do is touch my body.. ', Silenae taunts Darga agian, but she replies 'I know how weak you are, Silenae!'<br>
<br>
And the battle goes on. Finally, with her life ebbing away, Silenae tells Darga 'Come...', and the next strike finds its mark.<br>
<br>
Her death is the signal they have been waiting for. And despite the Scoundrel yelling 'Stop This nonsense Priestess Don't You Dare let harm come to kallee' Velsor and Shintou step forth and strike down the already wounded Darga. Defiance is in the Priestess voice as she adresses Falhurst : 'I will not'<br>
<br>
The silence is almost deafening, as the battle is over. But as the Priestess makes her way to where the two Teir'Dal have fallen, Falhurst advances to seek revenge, and another battle is joined. A very one sideded battle, as the knights and the mage ensure that no harm comes to the Priestess - even at the price of Falhurst's death.<br>
<br>
Ankhami kneels between the two bodies, praying to Innoruuk, and Silenae and Kallee - sent back to the world by the Prince of Hate, settle down to watch what will happen. Velsor asks 'Do you feel well, Kallee?', but unknowing of what is to come, she replies 'Feel well? Not likely.'. Behind her, Silenae stares at the floor.<br>
<br>
Ankhami takes out the sapphire and pricks her finger, mingles her blood with Silenae's drawing runes on one side muttering a prayer. Ankhami licks off the blood from her finger, takes some of Kallee's blood and draws runes on the other side, lifting the stone to the sky.<br>
She shouts out her request from Him <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    'The stone has been blessed in your name, Prince of Hate, Innoruuk. I call upon thee. The sacrafice has been made from the blood of your children. I come befor you as High Priestss to judge my worthyness, my blood sacrafice to you, in runes upon this gem to lock Darga L'Streea's soul to keep her from runing your plan for your children. I invoke the name of our god, Innoruuk, in his name comand thee, Darga L'Streea, enter into your new dwelling place'</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Ankhami shakes as the power from her god enfuses her body and the gem glowes with the spirit of Darga. Quickly, she places two more drops of her blood on the stone.<br>
A sigh of relief escapes Silenae as she hears Ankhami's voice shout out the final phrase of the ritual <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    'Let what has been done not be undone. These runes will pose as a warning to all, that the soul of Darga L'Streea resides with in'</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Carefully, Ankhami takes the stone and hides it from view, saying 'It is done'. Exhausted, she slumps to the ground, only to be gathered up by Kazanti, who returns her to the throne.<br>
<br>
Kallee closes her eyes for a moment to gain her bearings. She feels Silenae's touch on her hand, and hears her voice. 'too much death.' Still, she looks around in wonder, watched with by Silenae's sorrow filled eyes. Seeing Ankhami back on the throne, she makes her way over and kneels before her. 'I...I don't know how to thank you.'. Her words are rewarded with a smile, while from the side, Shintou asks 'Is she completly Cured from it.. now? Has Darga really gone for good?'<br>
Kallees eyes turn towards Shintou, and the priestess replies 'aye Darga's soul is bound within the gem'.<br>
<br>
From the other side, the magician comments 'i personally don't trust stones to hold spirits.. someone's always thinkin' they're worth stealing and sellin.' earning himself a glare from Silenae, and the hissed comment 'you are welcome to find a better vessel, Imp.'<br>
But his words struck a chord, and reminded Velsor of the lifeless body of Falhurst 'Speaking of stealing, where is Falhurst?', while Kallee asks 'Yes, Talru...what will happen with the stone?' 'no one will want to touch this stone' comes from the Priestess, who shivers as she speaks. She then looks to Kazanti and says 'i want to leave this place.'<br>
<br>
Silenae too shivers, sinking to her knees. The magician quickly steps over to her to offer his robe. 'i've enough heat inside me anyway.. ', which she takes to wrap herself in it.<br>
Kallee rises and thanks Shintou, before stepping over to Silenae. She wraps her arms around Silenae, holding the shaking woman. They seem to exchange a few thoughts, and in the end, Silenae relaxes, leaning against Kallee, who smiles at her.<br>
<br>
At this, Shintou takes his leave. He waves goodbye, bows before the Priestess, and mentiones 'Take care of her, Silenae.. Fight well, all of you..'. With a word of thanks from the Priestess, he turns to leave.<br>
<br>
Velsor too attempts to take his leave, but their departure is interrupted. Not all is well. The scoundrel, called back to his body by the powers of Innoruuk, wielded by Ankhami, is livid.<br>
And while Talru passes out wine for a celebration, another confrontation arises. Even Shintou's apology and attempted explanation cannot placate Falhurst. 'But it was for her own Good.. Please Understand.'<br>
<br>
The Knights gather around the resurrected Scoundrel. 'But it was for her own Good.. Please Understand.', Shintou metions, while saluting Falhurst. But it does nothing to ease the pain of betrayal. 'A day of Reckoning will come.........Mark My words.........Hell Hath No Fury Like a Falhurst SScorned' is the answer, hissed by Falhurst, who then spits on the ground before them. The Priestess nods, acknowledging the fury 'I am sorry, but it needed to be done', as do Kallee and the others. They try to expain.  'did you want her...the way she was?' comes from the Priestess 'with that demon in her?', while Kallee mentions 'It did, Falhurst, and I thank you for being with me. I am sorry...'. But all they earn is another snarl from Falhurst.<br>
<br>
Kallee tries to explain the fury 'He didn't know, Ankhami...he didn't see, and Silenae starts to speak, but belatedly decides agaisnt it.<br>
<br>
Falhursts Fury remained unchecked as he states 'I will have my Vengence in the time i see fit', which prompts the Knights to movie in closer, and Kazanti to step in front of the Priestess, who merely acknowledges the threat. 'I warn you all now' is the next thing said. 'I do Not forget'.<br>
<br>
Kallee tries to reason with him, asking 'Vengeance against whom? For what? Falhurst, it is done. I am Kallee now...and all these people came here to insure that.', while Ankhami offers herself to him. 'Falhurst... would it calm your soul to strike me now? For it is I that you are mad at'. But Falhurst does not accept either. 'I don't buy any of the Religous Nonsense All i know is today i was attacked by people who in the past claimed to be allies I will not forget betrayal'<br>
'Did you not attack first?', the Priestess asks. 'I asked you...not to', but he merely replies 'You know i will let no harm come to Kallee' 'None did.. she is whole now is her answer to that.' But as if he had not listened, he goes on 'And you a Priestess of Innoruuk stand by and watch while a Knight is attacked'<br>
<br>
Once again, Ankhami tries to reason. 'I could do nothing...Kallee's soul was at stake. Her SOUL, Falhurst.' But it is all for nothing.  'I will have my Vengence in the Time i see fit.......I warn you all once to watch your back You never know what lies in the shadows', he snarls as he stalks off, accompanied by a last question from the priestess. 'How many deaths would have happend...if darga had gained enough power to overcome ?'<br>
<br>
Silenae watches Falhurst for a moment, and then, with a deep sigh, she turns and stumbles back. Still with the sigh, she murmurs 'that price i was not willing to pay.' It seems this ritual caused more than in should have. The priestess too sighs disappointetly, as does Kallee, mentioning 'I...I don't think he can understand....'<br>
<br>
The mage brings it to the point: 'well... this doesn't look like quite the happy ending we were after.'<br>
<br>
The discussion turns to the vessel for a moment.. the stone. Kallee demands 'I want to know what will happen to the stone!', but all the priestess answers is 'it is gone'. Where, she demands, but again Ankhami evades the question 'a safe place'<br>
The mage intervenes asking 'why couldn't we have used a less expensive stone... that one was so... catching. ', which earns him a glare from Silenae, and the quick answer is .<br>
<br>
Ankhami turns to Kallee. 'you feel better?', she asks. 'I feel...it is so hard to explain.', and the priestess nods. 'I feel...oddly empty...and it is good.'. 'It will take time for you to heal...'<br>
<br>
Thinking of Falhurst, who stalked off, Kallee turns to go. 'I need to see to Falhurst...I think.' Silenae steps forward to join her. 'should i come with you, Kallee.. or should i better stay apart ?' 'I would wish you to come with, if you want to, Silenae.', Kallee replies. Silenae glances at the robe, stained in blood and mentions 'i wish to come, Kallee.. i do. But i fear his hatred might touch me too.', which Kallee answers with a simple hug. They both turn to the others to give thanks for the deed. 'I must leave...but I want to thank you all. I don't know....I don't know how.'. 'Kallee, was done by your request, no thanks is needed' is the simple explanation given by Ankhami, while Kazanti adds 'You are Abben... you where in need'<br>
<br>
In the end, the decision is made. After kneeling before Ankhami, Silenae says 'i will go with Kallee.. perhaps we can get Falhurst to see sense.', and both of them leave for the ice to find the Scoundrel. The priestess's blessing goes with them.'go with hate...may Innoruuk guide you, Kallee'.<br>
<br>
Ankhami too feels the need to leave. 'I want to leave this place', she says. 'I want to go home', and Kazanti replies 'Then we shall'. Before they leave, Ankhami stops and turns back to look at the platform, sadness filling her eyes.<br>
<br>
------------<br>
<br>
Epilogue<br>
<br>
This is not the end of the story. The powers used to trap the spirit are weak, and Darga is furious in her prison. She constantly wears at the sigils, and slowly, they begin to fail. And even now, plans are made to find a stronger prison for the spirti.<br>
<br>
Ankhami bears the burdon of the stone. And though it is a heavy load, she refuses all offers to share it.<br>
<br>
Kallee and Silenae too did not come to enjoy the following days together. With the freedom finally won, Kallee changes. For her, the days of battle are over. Knowing that Silenae does not yet feel that peace, and would attempt to keep her at her side, she decides to leave quietly, with one last glance at the Bonedancer who bought her freedom with her life. <br>
<br>
Kallee now lives peacefully in a place hidden away, and awaits notice from the Wizard who is trying to track down who killed her parents.. and why.<br>
<br>
Silenae still walks the world, but for her, things have turned cold. Words she spoke, later, while giving a small gift seem to have become true '<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   I spend my time in the ice. And my soul has become of ice. I wrap myself in it. That way, i can keep Kallee's memory, and remain untouched from the outside. What i gave you was the last piece which held some warmth... There will be no other.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'<br>
<br>
Nothing was seen of the Scoundrel after this. Tales are told that he haunted Skyshrine for a day, but after that, he vanished.<br>
